<a href="/questions/1566393-did-anyone-else-think-the-resolution-was">See all 23 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/54563180-andy-potts"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1459715802i/54563180._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/54563180-andy-potts">Andy Potts</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Absolutely, the last part of this book completely killed it for me. Completely unrealistic, he had clear connections to the victims, living witnesses <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Absolutely, the last part of this book completely killed it for me. Completely unrealistic, he had clear connections to the victims, living witnesses who had met and been tricked by 'Tobias' which he never had to answer for. A really appalling ending.<br />I was also hoping for much more character information for the narrator/main character. His character is so uneven, the author never really touches on why he wants to play a part in killing these woman, in one sentence he's appalled at the thought of them being tortured and killed but the next he's helping to pick a new victim. I get its meant to be 'for' his Millicent and because of his relationship with her, but I never felt like it was explained or gone into in enough detail to ever feel believable. <br /><br />Over all the story started off well and intriguing but by the end I gave it 2 stars and even that felt a bit generous.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
