<div id="review_2538901799" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2538901799" />
    <a title="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill"><img alt="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1584753242p2/72904050.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2538901799?book_show_action=true">Feb 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" href="/user/show/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill">Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill?shelf=edelweiss">edelweiss</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2538901799" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13882786402901729143"><br/>**** Yayyyy the paperback edition is out for this book today March 3rd!!! If you haven&apos;t read this, what the heck are you waiting for????? Thank you so much to Berkley Publications for having me along on this blog tour- here is my review from last year! I LOVE this book!******<br/><br/><br/>OMG OMG OMG!!! Yes I am speechless as I finished up my most anticipated book of the year! It not only lived up to my expectations, it far exceeded them! Whew, how is this a debut? I mean really I am floored that this is Sam</span>
  <span id="freeText13882786402901729143" style="display:none"><br />**** Yayyyy the paperback edition is out for this book today March 3rd!!! If you haven't read this, what the heck are you waiting for????? Thank you so much to Berkley Publications for having me along on this blog tour- here is my review from last year! I LOVE this book!******<br /><br /><br />OMG OMG OMG!!! Yes I am speechless as I finished up my most anticipated book of the year! It not only lived up to my expectations, it far exceeded them! Whew, how is this a debut? I mean really I am floored that this is Samantha Downing's first book. New thriller queen in the house!<br /><br />I am going to try my hardest not to give anything away, just know you really need to read this. This is one of the most unique and well spun thriller plots I have come across and believe me I have read plenty. Don't think this is another wife and husband thriller with a plot you have read before.<br /><br />Millicent and her husband have a fantastic loving marriage. Fifteen years of wedded bliss with two wonderful children. Living in the peaceful suburbs they are just the perfect little family. How do they keep their marriage so fresh and their love so strong? They must work hard to keep each other happy. OH my god you have no idea. I have never read about such a dysfunctional couple. I can only say I felt like Millicent was a pet tiger and her husband would secretly bring home fresh meat to feed her. LOL. I have no other way to describe what I read.<br /><br />It is great when you know from the very first chapter that you are going to love it. The writing style had a raw, edgy humor to it and that is my favorite! I can't quite explain why I got suckered into liking this couple. It is awful to say that no matter what they did, I just couldn't quite hate them. I really didn't want this book to end. I was so wrapped up in their story. When I least expected it this story took a crazy turn leaving me dumbfounded. Did I miss the clues? I think not, it was just so well spun.<br /><br />Obviously I loved the hell out of this book. I can't recommend it enough. I sure hope Samantha Downing is banging out a new book in the near future. I for one will be first in line trying to get my hands on it! Now excuse me while I lock all my eye drops up, you know just in case anyone gets any ideas.<br /><br />Thank you so much to Samantha Downing, Berkley and Edelweiss for this fantastic ARC!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13882786402901729143" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


