<span id="freeTextContainer12337865334659386601">*deep breathing to calm myself so I can write this review*<br/><br/>Ok so when I got this book in the mail I literally jumped up and down while holding it to my chest....aaaaannnd I may have squealed just a little bit. My boyfriend thinks I&apos;m a nutcase. <br/><br/>Samantha Downing&apos;s debut novel is de-friggin-licious. <br/><br/>Since the description for this story gives practically nothing away, I don&apos;t want to spoil the readers experience whatsoever with a detailed review. <br/><br/>The prose is precise and to the point, never once get</span>
  <span id="freeText12337865334659386601" style="display:none">*deep breathing to calm myself so I can write this review*<br /><br />Ok so when I got this book in the mail I literally jumped up and down while holding it to my chest....aaaaannnd I may have squealed just a little bit. My boyfriend thinks I'm a nutcase. <br /><br />Samantha Downing's debut novel is de-friggin-licious. <br /><br />Since the description for this story gives practically nothing away, I don't want to spoil the readers experience whatsoever with a detailed review. <br /><br />The prose is precise and to the point, never once getting bogged down with useless information just to fill space. The characters are thoroughly developed and I quickly developed a love/hate relationship with them, though not nearly as deep as the one they have between themselves. Though this story is a slow burn, it remains tantalizing throughout, and when the flames are finally stoked it quickly turns into purgatory for all involved. <br /><br />Wow, this is such a fun, page turning read.Twists and turns abound.This would make a crazy, dark and fun TV show.</span>
